{{Use British English|date=August 2011}} {{Use dmy dates|date=August 2011}} {{Infobox person |name = Angelica Mandy |image = Angelica-mandy-comicon.jpg |caption = Mandy at ComicCon |birth_name = Angelica Joyce Mandy |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1992|08|25}} |birth_place = [[Bath, Somerset|Bath]], England, UK |death_date = |death_place = |othername = |website = |years_active = 2004âpresent |occupation = Actress, Model |academyawards = |spouse = }} '''Angelica Joyce Mandy''' (born 25 August 1992) is an English actress, best known for her role in the ''[[Harry Potter]]'' [[Harry Potter (films)|film]]s as [[Gabrielle Delacour]].<ref name="imdb.com">[http://www.imdb.com/name/nm1701596/ Angelica Mandy] at the [[Internet Movie Database]]</ref>
==Acting career== Mandy's character, [[Supporting Harry Potter characters#Gabrielle Delacour|Gabrielle Delacour]], appeared in the fourth film, ''[[Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire (film)|Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire]]'' (2005). She is the younger sister of [[Fleur Delacour]], Triwizard Tournament Champion from [[Beauxbatons]]. The character reappeared in the seventh film, ''[[Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows â Part 1|Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows]]'', in which Fleur was married.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://snitchseeker.com/harry-potter-news/angelica-mandy-reprise-gabrielle-delacour-role-deathly-hallows-65993/|title=Angelica Mandy to reprise Gabrielle Delacour role for Deathly Hallows|date=22 July 2009|accessdate=22 July 2009|publisher=SnitchSeeker}}</ref>
Mandy also played young [[:Becky Sharp]], a young version of [[Reese Witherspoon]]'s character in the film ''[[Vanity Fair (2004 film)|Vanity Fair]]'' (2004),<ref name="imdb.com"/> which was directed by [[:Mira Nair]].
Mandy's most recent film work has been in the short film ''The End'' in which she plays the character Frankie.
==Personal life== Mandy was born in [[Bath, Somerset|Bath]], England. She is interested in acting work, either as a [[Casting (performing arts)|casting director]], actress, or some other part of show business. She took a [[gap year]] after completing school.<ref>[http://angelicamandy.celebfans.net/aboutangelica.html Career Info]</ref>{{Dead link|date=March 2011}}
